article.headline: (10) DELAWARE ST 58, (9) NORTHRN ARIZONA 53
article.story: FLAGSTAFF, Ariz. (AP) -- Nathan Geiser scored 18 points and Northern Arizona's defense forced 32 turnovers as the Lumberjacks beat Fort Lewis College 86-74 in an exhibition game Friday night. Tyrone Bazy added 17 points and Ruben Boykin Jr. had 16 for NAU, which led by as many as 16 points in the first half. But the Lumberjacks couldn't shake the Skyhawks until late in the second half when Boykin's low-post basket sparked an 11-1 run. Devon Manning led Fort Lewis with 16 points while Guy Meyer had 12 points and six rebounds.
